pulltitle: Fixes typo in getting syslog_priority from config
pullsbody: Dots are replaced with underscores by default, so syslog.priority will never be present in config dictionary.
pull_commit_message:
Fixes typo in getting syslog_priority from config

Dots are replaced with underscores by default, so syslog.priority will never be present in config dictionary.

pullsbody:
This is a patch to the CEF library to allow messages to be encoded as unicode strings.

See: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=958690

This is required by heka-py as python-protobuf requires either 7-bit clean ASCII or unicode strings.

pullsbody:
Per https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=779371

LOG_PERROR is not defined on all platforms, this patch checks for its existence before sucking it into the _SYSLOG_OPTIONS dict.
pull_commit_message: Allow for syslog.LOG_PERROR being undefined on some platforms.
